<theorem xml:id="lecture-notes-formula-for-the-vertex-of-a-parabola">
  <title>Formula for the Vertex of a Parabola</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Let <m>f(x)=ax^2+bx+c</m> be a quadratic function. Then the formula for the vertex is</p>
    <p><me>(h,k)=\left(-\frac{b}{2a},f\left(-\frac{b}{2a}\right)\right)</me></p>
    <p>We can also rewrite this as the pair of equations</p>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>h\amp=-\frac{b}{2a} \amp k\amp=f\left(\frac{-b}{2a}\right)</mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
  </statement>
</theorem>

