<theorem xml:id="lecture-notes-height-of-projectiles">
  <title>Height of Projectiles</title>
  <statement>
    <p>
      The height of a projectile (in feet, ignoring air resistance) is given by the equation
      <me>h(t) = -16t^2 + v_0t + h_0,</me>
      where <m>v_0</m> is the initial velocity (in feet per second) and <m>h_0</m> is the initial height (in feet).
    </p>
  </statement>
</theorem>

